    "movements": [
      {
        "turn": 1,
        "name": "Act 1",
        "intent": "[The hearing room settles under a hard white morning, salt still drying on boots and coat hems. A blank place waits at the clerk's table, as if the first paper laid there will decide what kind of night the room is willing to remember.]"
      },
      {
        "turn": 5,
        "name": "Act 2",
        "intent": "[The clerk closes the wet book without triumph, and the room feels the weight of a number that has not yet chosen a tower. The next act opens under a lower ceiling: certainty must pass through sealed doors, official hands, and the hush of a lamp that may have had no right to speak.]"
      },
      {
        "turn": 10,
        "name": "Act 3",
        "intent": "[The chart is left open on the table, but no one leans over it now. The room changes its hunger: less for coastlines and more for marks a hand might have left in darkness.]"
      },
      {
        "turn": 16,
        "name": "Act 4",
        "intent": "[The ledgers are closed, and the room seems suddenly too narrow for paper. Rain comes harder against the windows; every face turns toward the door, waiting for the night itself to be brought in.]"
      }
    ],
    "tutorNotes": []
  },
